cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for feature reconfiguration, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of semantic information, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed architecture also involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with a basic SSD system, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
